s goals</li><li>Anticipation vs. Reaction: Think about what lies ahead and plan accordingly</li><li>Automate the World: Elimination of manual processes is key. If you have done it more than twice, it should be automated</li><li>Agile Junkie: DevOps is a part of Engineering &ndash; stories, sprints, bugs, and all</li><li>Efficient Process Builder: Bring enough process to the table to maximize efficiency and minimize wasted time/effort</li></ul><p><strong>Key Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Web application frameworks (Django highly desirable)</li><li>Exceptional skill in at least one programming language (Python scores extra points)</li><li>Deep experience with Amazon Web Services (EC2, S3, ELB, etc.)</li><li>Data stores&mdash;architecture and management (MongoDB, Redis, MySQL, etc.)</li><li>Caching and Load Balancing (Varnish, HAProxy, etc.)</li><li>Configuration Management tools (e.g. Puppet, Chef)</li><li>Automation and programmatic approach to scalability</li><li>Strong familiarity with Git or similar SCM</li><li>Troubleshooting (especially under fire)</li><li>Monitoring, alerting, dashboard, operational tools development skills</li><li>Loves writing documentation</li><li>Understands operational support of development teams</li><li>Speaks and writes English fluently</li><li>Sense of urgency and thrives in an incredibly fast-paced environment</li></ul><p>We actively use everything mentioned under &quot;Key Skills.&quot; Depending upon previous roles, similar skills/technologies may be equally acceptable.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Unless incapacitated, you may be the last thing standing between eternal glory and a flaming mess spinning quickly into oblivion.</p>]]></description>
